    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You can do:\r\n\r\n- `ipython --matplotlib auto` to setup interactive matplotlib without importing anything into the global namespace\r\n- `ipython --pylab auto` to import everything into the global namespace\r\n- set `c.InteractiveShellApp.pylab_import_all = False` in your `ipython_config.py` to change the default import behavior of `--pylab` above\r\n- set the same flag on the command-line for a single call: `ipython --pylab auto --InteractiveShellApp.pylab_import_all=False`\r\n- pass arbitrary lines of execution to initialize IPython: `ipython -i -c \"%pylab --no-import-all\"`\r\n\r\nTechnically, all options that can be set in a profile can be set on the command-line (replace `c.Class.trait = value` with `--Class.trait=value`), but the args quickly become too long to type out regularly. Setting preferences in a config file is generally the better way to go, unless it's really for a one-off deviation from your preferences."
